Three streams within the Milwaukee River watershed in Wisconsin, USA were monitored for human and bovine viruses over a 17 month period, February 2007 to June 2008 (Table 1
, Fig. 1
). One site was composed mainly of rural land use (Cedar Creek) and the other was mainly urban land use (Underwood Creek). The third site was at the mouth of the Milwaukee River which includes a mix of different land uses. The Milwaukee River monitoring site was located downstream of input from Cedar and Underwood Creeks.
